<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,631,800]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,703,728]" pageId="2">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described originally as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1817" box="[828,993,703,728]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,993,703,728]" italics="true" pageId="2">Trachyphloeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" box="[1070,1436,703,728]" pageId="2" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler (2013)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to a new genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Borovec &amp; Oberprieler, 2013" authorityName="Borovec &amp; Oberprieler" authorityYear="2013" box="[492,972,740,765]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrophloeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[492,628,740,765]" italics="true" pageId="2">Afrophloeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" box="[636,972,740,765]" pageId="2" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, placed in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1942" box="[1199,1321,740,765]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Embrithini">Embrithini</taxonomicName>
Marshall, 1942. The 
<typeStatus box="[271,374,775,800]" pageId="2">lectotype</typeStatus>
was examined and designated as such by 
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" box="[845,1190,775,800]" pageId="2" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
